Morgan Stanley (MS)  may sell its wealth-
management unit in India after a review of the business, said a
person with knowledge of the matter.  The four-year-old business is headed by Executive Director
Himanshu Bhagat based in  Mumbai . A final decision on the sale
will be taken in two months, according to the person, who
declined to be identified as the plan isnâ€™t public.  Reuters reported on the proposal earlier. Morgan Stanley
declined to comment on the report in an e-mail.  To contact the reporter on this story:
